The thinking process itself may also be distinguished as material or formal. It is formal when the matter given is sufficient for the completion of the product, without any other addition than what is communicated in the act of thought itself. It is material when the data are insufficient aud the mind has consequently to go out of the thinking act to obtain additional materials.
